				<font face="verdana" size="2" color="black">
				Thanks for the assumptions, Revaryn, but you might want to check your breathless defense of your pal at the door and take a deep breath for a moment.<BR>
<BR>
First, many of the censored posts on Banegrivm's boards were posted in an intelligent, non-condescending manner free of insults and such things as &quot;role play sucks&quot;.  I myself am a roleplayer and disagree with Banegrivm's way of thinking -- don't assume everything is stark black and white.  He has removed reasonable posts that merely differed from his views in the past, and I do not doubt he would do so again.<BR>
<BR>
As for copyright laws... think very closely about that word.  &quot;Copyright&quot;.  The right to copy.  Banegrivm reposted exact paragraphs from Sony's official site, reposted their property, without permission and without even giving them due credit -- before you go laughing in the face of someone who suggests that he may indeed have violated copyright laws, perhaps you should read up on said things.<BR>
